Landing page design spec (`resources/js/pages/Landing.vue`):

- Structure: single-column flow inside full-height `main`; section order fixed: top controls, examples CTA, hero, projects, contact, footer.
- Theme: neutral base palette with dark/light toggle; preserve smooth theme transition (`300ms`) for background/text.
- Accent system: one selected accent color drives key highlights and text selection via CSS vars (`--selection-bg`, `--accent-color`).
- Typography: body/headings use Inter; code/tech labels use JetBrains Mono.
- Motion: color transitions `300ms` cubic-bezier; micro interactions (scroll-fade, hover scale, CTA opacity/transform) stay `200ms` ease.
- Navigation behavior: hash `#projects` and CTA action both smooth-scroll to projects section.
- Component boundary: keep page as composition/orchestration layer; section visuals and content live in dedicated `landing/*Section.vue` components.

When editing Landing UI, keep these constraints unless user explicitly requests a redesign.
